 {"id": "franken_networkx-codtrav-review", "title": "[HIGH] REVIEW: topological_sort tie-break order diverges from NetworkX", "description": "The cod traversal conformance matrix found topological_sort on a diamond DAG with insertion order [('s','a'), ('s','b'), ('a','c'), ('b','c')] returns ['s','b','a','c'] in fnx while upstream NetworkX returns ['s','a','b','c']. The output is a valid topological order but diverges from NetworkX-observable insertion-order tie policy.", "status": "closed", "priority": 1, "issue_type": "bug", "created_at": "2026-04-24T05:46:30.366748Z", "created_by": "codex", "updated_at": "2026-04-24T06:11:00.950758Z", "source_repo": ".", "compaction_level": 0, "original_size": 0, "closed_at": "2026-04-24T06:11:00.950758Z", "close_reason": "Fixed: topological_sort reimplemented in Python using Kahn's algorithm with FIFO insertion-order queue. MultiDiGraph parity preserved by counting parallel edges in indegree. nx-observable tie-break order now byte-matches."}
